cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category as it introduces bio-inspired artificial neural networks consisting of neurons that are additionally characterized by spatial positions. It may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category as it discusses interpretability and continual learning. Additionally, it may fall under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category as it proposes a new approach to neural network architecture. The Systems and Control (cs.SY) category may also be relevant as the paper discusses the behavior of the network as a system. Finally, the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category may be relevant as the paper discusses the processing of different tasks by different clusters of neurons.
